comments: Green (TOR) is firming up and makes marginal contact with DeRozan (TOR) while setting the pick.
Siakam (TOR) moves laterally into the path of Bertans (SAS) on the drive and dislodges him.
Siakam (TOR) makes marginal contact with Mills (SAS) while firming up on the pick.
Siakam (TOR) makes marginal contact with Mills (SAS) off ball that does not affect his ability to defend the pass in the post.
Lowry (TOR) makes tactile contact to the body of DeRozan (SAS) during his shooting motion that does not affect his post play and turnaround jump shot attempt.
Aldridge (SAS) extends his arms into Ibaka (TOR), but he is still able to grab the rebound and make his intended pass.
Belinelli (SAS) makes marginal contact to the arm of Siakam (TOR) during his shooting motion that does not affect his shot attempt.
Leonard (TOR) places an arm to the front of DeRozan (SAS) during the drive but the contact does not affect his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] Leonard (TOR) lifts his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Aldridge (SAS) makes marginal contact to the body of Leonard (TOR) at the end of the drive.
Mills (SAS) makes contact to Ibaka's (TOR) arm prior to his shot attempt.
Leonard (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position and reaches in to attempt to steal the ball from DeRozan (SAS) and DeRozan loses his balance and control of the ball on his own.
Belinelli (SAS) and Leonard (TOR) briefly engage and disengage during the pick.
Lowry (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position during the jump shot attempt by Bertans (SAS).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of Spurs ball is overturned to Raptors ball.

Leonard (TOR) never has possession in the frontcourt when he makes contact with the inbound pass and his momentum carries him into the backcourt, where the pass was directed, and he establishes a positive position and legally gains possession.  During inbound passes that are directed to the backcourt in the last two minutes of the 4th quarter and overtime periods, frontcourt or backcourt status is not attained until a player with the ball has established a positive position in either half.
White (SAS) commits a take foul on Leonard (TOR).
